THE GAME
--------

  'DoorMaze' is a Workbench game where the goal is to get to the
exit by exploring a 99 by 99 spaces area where you only see a 5 by
5 spaces portion of it. To move about, you have to open 'doors'
(represented by horizontal or vertical bars) that are located next
to your position. Sometimes, these doors are replaced by brick
walls, which you have to get around, as you cannot go through.

  To complicate matters a bit, the exit, located somewhere on the
edge of the game area, is surrounded by coloured doors which must
be unlocked by a corresponding coloured key, which has to be found
somewhere in the game area. The game is simple to play, but
finding the appropriate key to unlock one of the exit access doors
is the key, so to speak, to the game...!

  Complete the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

